rComments: She has cold personality, and the TA was so poor.

Excellent teacher. She's really enthusiastic about the material, and encourages class participation without being pushy. Midterms are pretty easy, paper topics are interesting and relevant, and the material itself is really cool. Lots of fascinating videos, experiments used as examples. Most people I know really wanted to go to lecture every time.

she is a new teacher but very good. her lectures were very interesting. for a person who has a hard time getting to class, i wanted to go every time. she had fun demonstrations. she never picked on anyone but gave candy to participants in the demonstrations. midterms not too bad, papers pretty good.

Julie is a new professor at UCSC and it seems as though she's still learning the ropes, but is open to suggestions from students. Her lectures are pretty entertaining and she does a lot of demonstrations but doesn't put people on the spot. 2 Midterms, 2 papers, and a final. The paper topics are pretty bad, but the tests were ok.
